    pageItem P3210_GREENBUTTON_FLG (
        type: switch
        label {
            label: Green Button Enabled?
            alignment: left
        }
        layout {
            sequence: 200
            region: @green-button-information
            slot: regionBody
            alignment: left
            columnSpan: 4
        }
        appearance {
            template: @optional-floating
            templateOptions: #DEFAULT#
        }
        source {
            formRegion: @livelabs-publishing-info
            column: GREENBUTTON_FLG
            dataType: varchar2
        }
        help {
            helpText: "Enabling this switch does not mean that your workshop will have a Green Button in LiveLabs automatically. In order to create a Green Button, please view the section below title 'Green Button Questionnaire'. After completing that section, make sure to email livelabs-help-db_us@oracle.com to get started with your Green Button. "
        }
    )

    pageItem P3210_GREENBUTTON_INFO (
        type: richTextEditor
        label {
            alignment: left
        }
        settings {
            format: html
            minHeight: 180
        }
        layout {
            sequence: 270
            region: @green-button-information
            slot: regionBody
            alignment: left
        }
        appearance {
            template: @optional-above
            templateOptions: [
                #DEFAULT#
                margin-top-none
            ]
        }
        source {
            formRegion: @livelabs-publishing-info
            column: GREENBUTTON_INFO
            dataType: clob
        }
        default {
            type: static
            staticValue:
                ```
                Please fill out our Green Button Questionnaire to determine if this workshop can be run on a registered LiveLabs Tenancy.<br><br>
                
                <b>NOTE: Not all resources in OCI are supported by LiveLabs. If the LiveLabs team encounters such a resource in your request, we will reach out to determine if there is another option.</b>
                
                <br><br>
                
                <b><u>BASIC QUESTIONS</u></b>
                <ol>
                <li>Does your green button require access to Cloud Shell?
                    <ul>
                    <li>Yes or No</li>
                    </ul></li>
                <li>Does your green button require a VCN? (LiveLabs can provision a VCN as a part of the reservation setup with our standard Security List)
                    <ul>
                    <li>Yes or No</li>
                    </ul></li>
                <li>If yes, please list the ports that must be opened for the function of your workshop:
                    <ul>
                    <li>Example: 129.146.0.0/21 port 22</li>
                    <li></li>
                    </ul></li>
                <li>List all resources that need to be provisioned by LiveLabs for your workshop (do not list any resources that the user will spin up):
                    <ul>
                    <li>Example: OKE Cluster - 1 Node</li>
                    <li></li>
                    </ul></li>
                <li>List all resources that the user will provision while running the workshop (do not list any resources provisioned by LiveLabs):
                    <ul>
                    <li>Example: ADW - 1 OCPU</li>
                    <li>Example: ADW - 1 TB</li>
                    <li></li>
                    </ul></li>
                <li>Does your green button require a terraform script?
                    <ul>
                    <li><b>If yes,</b> please attend LiveLabs Office Hours to determine how best to proceed with the creation of your green button</li>
                    </ul></li>
                </ol>
                
                <br>
                <b><u>POLICIES</u><br></b>
                Please list all of the policies that users will need to complete your workshop. This should include access to the resources provisioned by LiveLabs as well as the resources that the users need to create/edit/delete.<br>
                <ul>
                <li>Example: Allow user to manage autonomous-database-family</li>
                <li></li>
                </ul>
                
                
                <br>
                <b><u>IMAGE AND MARKETPLACE QUESTIONS</u></b>
                <ol>
                <li>Does your green button require the use of an image from OCI Marketplace?
                    <ul>
                    <li>Yes or No</li>
                    </ul></li>
                <li>Does your require image already exist and is used by another LiveLabs Green Button?
                    <ul>
                    <li><b>If yes,</b> please provide the WMS and LiveLabs ID for the workshop:
                        <ul>
                        <li>WMS ID:</li>
                        <li>LiveLabs ID:</li>
                        </ul>
                        </li>
                    <li><b>If no,</b> you will need to create a Marketplace Image and Listing for your green button. Please attend LiveLabs Office Hours for assistance with this. After creating your image, please provide the following:
                        <ul>
                        <li>Marketplace App Listing OCID:</li>
                        <li>Marketplace Image OCID:</li>
                        <li>Marketplace Listing Resource Version: </li>
                        </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                </ol>
                
                
                <br>
                <b><u>ADDITIONAL INFORMATION</u></b><br>
                Please provide any addition information to the LiveLabs team that is pertinent to your Green Button that you haven't detailed above:
                <ul><li></li></ul>
                
                <br/> <br/> <br/> --------------------------------NOTES FROM LIVELABS ADMIN--------------------------------<br>(For Official Use Only)<br>
                ```
        }
    )

